paragraph.content:
that the document was so produced under the direction of a person having
                    practical knowledge of and experience in the use of computers as a means of
                    storing, processing or retrieving information;

such person was at the time of certifying the document appointed under
                    subsection (2) to certify transcripts of records in such other language;
                    and

section.def:
court
                (法院、法庭)
            includes any tribunal;

document
                (文件) means anything in which information of any
            description is recorded;

paragraph.content:
means a statement made otherwise than by a person while giving oral
                    evidence in the proceedings which is tendered as evidence of the matters
                    stated;

proceedings at first instance in the High Court or in the Supreme Court of
                    England as constituted by section 1 of the Courts Act 1971 (1971 c.
                    23 U.K.);

any power of a court, in any legal proceedings, to exclude evidence
                    (whether by preventing questions from being put or otherwise) at its discretion;
                    or

section.def:
live audio-visual link (音視直播聯繫) has the meaning given by section 2
            of the Courts (Remote Hearing) Ordinance (6 of 2025);
                (Added 6 of 2025 s. 65)

paragraph.content:
supported by a statement contained in the request (whether it is so
                    supported unconditionally or subject to conditions that are fulfilled);
                    or

subparagraph.content:
in respect of such first-mentioned document, the conditions mentioned
                        in that subsection in relation to a document of that kind are satisfied;
                        and

shall have been made by a person having custody or control of any
                            record, book or document from which the foreign document is
